AB  - The main objective of this work is to identify affirmative measures that contribute to reduce vulnerabilities and reinforce gender equality in the opportunities presented by the climate change adaptation measures implemented in three municipalities of Cuba (Los Palacios, Güira de Melena and Jimaguayú). Participatory workshops were carried out with municipal gender technical teams under the coordination of a national gender team to identify affirmative actions that could close the gender gaps identified in previous diagnoses. These actions should be integrated into the general proposal for measures to adapt to climate change that are implemented in each municipality. In total, five affirmative measures were defined, two to be implemented in the municipality of Los Palacios, one in the municipality Güira de Melena, one in the municipality Jimaguayú and one general for the three municipalities. The actions involve, on the one hand, the implementation of agricultural practices and technologies with the participation and preferential management of women, such as posture and semi-protected crops, organic matter production centers, minindustry, conservation agriculture, Rainwater in rural homes, among others. It also defines measures for training, communication and community advocacy as well as for achieving economic autonomy and female leadership in the process of adaptation at the local level.
