AB  - The article focuses on the alarming state of hunger and malnutrition in Asia, highlighting that nearly half a billion people in the region are undernourished despite economic growth. A report from the U.N.'s Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) reveals stagnation in progress against hunger, with significant increases in severe food insecurity, particularly in South and Southeast Asia. The report emphasizes the dual challenges of malnutrition and obesity among children, exacerbated by reliance on unhealthy processed foods and poor access to clean water and sanitation. It also notes the impact of climate change-related disasters on food availability and the prevalence of open defecation, which poses health risks and increases vulnerability for women and girls.
