AB  - The article focuses on the speech delivered by Hilda Flavia Nakabuye, a 22-year-old Ugandan college student and founder of #FridaysForFuture Uganda, at the C40 Mayors summit in Copenhagen. Nakabuye highlights the severe impacts of climate change on her community, including droughts and crop failures, which have affected her education and livelihood. She emphasizes the urgency of climate action and calls on global leaders and youth to unite in the fight for a sustainable future, expressing her determination to advocate for change despite the challenges faced. Nakabuye's message reflects the broader movement of youth activists inspired by figures like Greta Thunberg, urging immediate action against climate change.
