AB  - Information about the panel discussion "Linking Rivers, Barrages and Fish Migration" held at the KUFOS Seminar Hall in Kochi, Kerala, India on May 21, 2016 is presented. Topics include the impact of regulating fluvial systems using dams, barrages, and inter-basin link canals on fish populations, the collapse of riverine fisheries-based livelihoods in the country, and the native impact of climate change on fish behaviour. Lecturers at the event includes Parineeta Dandekar and Mara Pandian.
