AB  - Highlights: [•] There is no evidence for agricultural extensification across areas in East Africa. [•] Food insecurity is common at all sites with an annual rainfall of 800mm or less. [•] Households pursue diversification also where livestock is crucial for livelihoods. [•] Opportunistic cropping is seen as a diversification strategy in low rainfall places. [•] Systems are in transition but the changes are not necessarily climate driven.
